Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive report:

## AI SDK Provider Package Structure - Complete Analysis

I've thoroughly explored both the OpenAI and FAL provider packages to understand the structure needed for creating a new provider. Here's your detailed blueprint:

---

### 1. PACKAGE.JSON STRUCTURE

**Location:** `/packages/<provider-name>/package.json`

Both packages follow this standard pattern:

```json
{
  "name": "@ai-sdk/<provider-name>",
  "version": "X.X.X",
  "license": "Apache-2.0",
  "sideEffects": false,
  "main": "./dist/index.js",
  "module": "./dist/index.mjs",
  "types": "./dist/index.d.ts",
  "files": [
    "dist/**/*",
    "docs/**/*",
    "src",
    "!src/**/*.test.ts",
    "!src/**/*.test-d.ts",
    "!src/**/__snapshots__",
    "!src/**/__fixtures__",
    "CHANGELOG.md",
    "README.md"
  ],
  "scripts": {
    "build": "pnpm clean && tsup --tsconfig tsconfig.build.json",
    "build:watch": "pnpm clean && tsup --watch",
    "clean": "del-cli dist docs *.tsbuildinfo",
    "prepack": "mkdir -p docs && cp ../../content/providers/01-ai-sdk-providers/XX-<provider>.mdx ./docs/",
    "postpack": "del-cli docs",
    "type-check": "tsc --build",
    "test": "pnpm test:node && pnpm test:edge",
    "test:update": "pnpm test:node -u",
    "test:watch": "vitest --config vitest.node.config.js",
    "test:edge": "vitest --config vitest.edge.config.js --run",
    "test:node": "vitest --config vitest.node.config.js --run"
  },
  "exports": {
    "./package.json": "./package.json",
    ".": {
      "types": "./dist/index.d.ts",
      "import": "./dist/index.mjs",
      "require": "./dist/index.js"
    }
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "@ai-sdk/provider": "workspace:*",
    "@ai-sdk/provider-utils": "workspace:*"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "@ai-sdk/test-server": "workspace:*",
    "@types/node": "20.17.24",
    "@vercel/ai-tsconfig": "workspace:*",
    "tsup": "^8",
    "typescript": "5.8.3",
    "zod": "3.25.76"
  },
  "peerDependencies": {
    "zod": "^3.25.76 || ^4.1.8"
  },
  "engines": {
    "node": ">=18"
  },
  "publishConfig": {
    "access": "public"
  },
  "homepage": "https://ai-sdk.dev/docs",
  "repository": {
    "type": "git",
    "url": "git+https://github.com/vercel/ai.git"
  }
}
```

**Key patterns:**
- Workspace dependencies using `workspace:*`
- Both CJS and ESM exports via tsup
- Standard test scripts for both node and edge environments
- Optional "internal" export path (OpenAI includes this, FAL doesn't)

---

### 2. TSCONFIG.JSON STRUCTURE

**Location:** `/packages/<provider-name>/tsconfig.json` and `/packages/<provider-name>/tsconfig.build.json`

**tsconfig.json:**
```json
{
  "extends": "./node_modules/@vercel/ai-tsconfig/ts-library.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "composite": true,
    "rootDir": "src",
    "outDir": "dist"
  },
  "exclude": [
    "dist",
    "build",
    "node_modules",
    "tsup.config.ts"
  ],
  "references": [
    {
      "path": "../provider"
    },
    {
      "path": "../provider-utils"
    }
  ]
}
```

**tsconfig.build.json:**
```json
{
  "extends": "./tsconfig.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "composite": false
  }
}
```

---

### 3. SRC/INDEX.TS EXPORTS PATTERN

**Standard export format:**
```typescript
// Provider factory and interface
export type { YourProvider, YourProviderSettings } from './your-provider';
export { createYour, your } from './your-provider';

// Model-specific options/types
export type {
  YourImageModelOptions,
  // Deprecated aliases for backwards compatibility
  YourImageModelOptions as YourImageProviderOptions,
} from './your-image-options';
export type { YourSpeechModelOptions } from './your-speech-model';
export type { YourTranscriptionModelOptions } from './your-transcription-model';
export type { YourVideoModelId } from './your-video-settings';

// Version export
export { VERSION } from './version';
```

**Key patterns:**
- One default provider export (factory function + singleton)
- Type exports for each model type's options
- Deprecated aliases for backwards compatibility
- VERSION export injected at build time

**Location examples:**
- `/packages/openai/src/index.ts` (17 lines - multi-model provider)
- `/packages/fal/src/index.ts` (16 lines - multi-model provider)

---

### 4. IMAGE GENERATION MODEL IMPLEMENTATION

**Location:** `/packages/<provider-name>/src/<provider>-image-model.ts`

**Required Interface:** `ImageModelV3` from `@ai-sdk/provider`

